['\n<p>\n\t<span style="font-size:18px;"><strong>Protecting The Seas</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n\t<a href="https://www.sailorsforthesea.org/programs/clean-regattas/registered-events" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="data:image/png;base64," style="width: 167px; height: 200px;" /></a></p>\n<p>\n\tHowth Yacht Club joined forces with our friends at <a href="https://www.sailorsforthesea.org/programs/clean-regattas/registered-events" target="_blank"><strong><em><span style="color:#0000cd;"><u>Sailors For The Sea</u></span></em></strong></a> in 2014. Since then, we have made 8 large regattas cleaner and greener and helped to protect the seas we play in. At <a href="https://www.waveregatta.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color:#0000cd;"><strong><em><u>WAVE Regatta</u></em></strong></span></a> in 2022, we estimated we saved over 2,000 single-use plastic bottles in 3 days by all the sailors having their own water bottles and providing a filtered water fountain in the dinghy park!</p>\n<p>\n\tFor the 2023 Youth Nationals, we will try to achieve the Gold standard and that means we all need to make an effort.</p>\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tWe will not have single-use plastics.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tWe will make sure our RIB engines are turned off when we are not moving.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tWe will walk or cycle and share cars to and from the event every day.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n\tThese small little things and others will combine to create one big result.</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>Recycling and Waste</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n\tThere are green bins throughout the dinghy pen.</p>\n<p>\n\tOn the water, official RIBs will take any waste you want to dispose of.</p>\n<p>\n\tThe after-sailing food will be served in biodegradable trays. Please put these in the black bins when you have eaten</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>Prizes</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n\tThere will be some really special prizes awarded at the end of the Championships for the sailors that show how passionate they are for looking after our lovely seas.</p>\n']
